# Web Security Checklist

This repository provides a comprehensive checklist for web security based on industry standards and best practices.

## Table of Contents
- [Introduction](#introduction)
- [Checklist](#checklist)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [Resources](#resources)
- [License](#license)

## Introduction
The Web Security Checklist is designed to help developers and security professionals ensure the security of web applications. It covers a wide range of security topics, including but not limited to:

- Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
- Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)
- SQL Injection
- Clickjacking
- Secure Session Management
- Input Validation
- Secure Communication (HTTPS)
- Server Configuration
- Access Control
- Error Handling
- Logging and Monitoring
- Vulnerability Scanning
- Penetration Testing

Each checklist item includes a brief description and references to additional resources for further reading.

## Checklist
The checklist is organized into different sections based on the security topics. Please refer to each section for the detailed checklist items and recommended best practices.

